Q.12: A sum of Rs 700 is to be used to give seven cash prizes to students of a school for their overall academic performance. If each prize is Rs 20 less than its preceding prize, find the value of each of the prizes.
Solution: Let the cost of 1st prize be Rs.P.
Cost of 2nd prize = Rs.P − 20
And cost of 3rd prize = Rs.P − 40
We can see that the cost of these prizes is in the form of A.P., having a common difference as −20 and first term as P.
Thus, a = P and d = −20
